<p>Hey Emil,</p>
<p>Everyone’s mind is different, and there’s no wrong or right way to use it. Here’s how I find myself using mymind on a daily basis:</p>
<p> <br />
✨ When an idea strikes me (on the train, in the shower, in bed, etc.) or I want to remember something I need to do, I reach for my phone and quickly make a note in mymind before I forget it. Often, I’ll go into Focus Mode later to expand on my notes or drafts.</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/eRydL6LNBfGew6wb9s1YhF;870x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p> <br />
✨ When I’m browsing social media and see a visual or post that inspires me or makes me laugh, I right click and save it. Even if it's deleted later from social media, it will be safe in mymind <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XtpqVuR-K-s&list=PLTMivYhZncwh4QDoHobfQCvb6JdvNtifT&index=9" style="color: #FF5924;">(mymind can even read and find text in my memes &amp; screenshots!)</a></p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/8cpF7NLSVsYeMr9TztwtTm;872x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p> <br />
✨ When I’m shopping online, I save dozens of products I’m considering to mymind (sometimes I’ll even make <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pBwT_7ZZl8A" style="color: #FF5924;">a Smart Space</a> around a specific product on my wishlist).</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/eMHAINamqNTevw39NIB4dx;872x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>Something about “keeping” the link satisfies the urge to buy it right away. Sometimes I come back later and decide I do want to purchase it. Other times I realize I don’t want or need it at all, so I delete it from mymind and move on.</p>
<p> <br />
✨ Or when I’m in a meeting and need to make quick notes or a to-do list, I open up a Note in mymind.</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/a7Q6Jd50VigeMMFmaK4Gtn;870x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p> <br />
✨ When I find a product interesting or delicious or unique, I take a photo of it and save it to mymind. I have many photos of wrappers, bottles and packaging that don’t necessarily look curated or pretty on their own, but become beautiful as part of the little treasure trove I’ve created in mymind. (Besides, I’m the only one seeing it. So if I want it in there, it doesn’t matter how it looks.)</p>
<img src="https://carbon-media.accelerator.net/00000000001/b5Di1wsxm8ad0pB7Fby79e;870x540.png?auto=webp" width="960" height="463" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;"/>
<p>I hope you’ve discovered your own ways of using mymind, and that it already feels like it was made just for you.</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br />
Tobias,<br />
mymind co-founder</p>
